Moins de personnes.(Avis d'origine)We visited on the 4th of January, at a very popular period.The entrance to the park was pretty smooth. Lots of entrances, so the crowd spread evenly, and we all entered quite promptly.Our 4- and 5- year old were ecstatic when we entered the area.The show however were really those parades. Those are not to be missed.We did visit most of the rides that we were allowed to, but those parades are something else. Those are captured in the kids' memory for weeks to come.We visited early in the morning, and comparing with later on it was the best time to do so. Less people and less queues. As time went by, more people were coming and the queues were unbearable.A very enjoyable experience for the kids, and one that we may redo in a few years.Tips:-Food is overpriced. They are worth the time and effort to find a good spot.-Go in the morning. Less people.
